properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued December 31 at 7:35PM AKST until January 1 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Blizzard Warning, blizzard conditions frequently
reducing the visibility to near zero. Additional snow
accumulations of up to one inch. Winds gusting as high as 40
mph. For the Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills. Wind
chills as low as 45 below zero.

* WHERE...Blizzard conditions along the coast. Entire Kuskokwim
Delta for the wind chill.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM Wednesday for the Blizzard. Until noon AKST
Wednesday for the wind chill.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause frostbite
on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes. Near zero visibility
will make travel very difficult.
properties.instruction:
A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you.If you get stranded, stay
with your vehicle.

Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM AKST WEDNESDAY ALONG THE COAST OF THE KUSKOKWIM DELTA... ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON AKST WEDNESDAY
